<subSubSection pageNumber="305" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="305">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="305">Note: A.</emphasis>
later homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1753)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1755" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Antirrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="molle">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="305">A. molle</emphasis>
L. (1753)
</taxonomicName>
and hence illegitimate. Linnaeus subsequently realised his error in giving the same name to two different species, renaming this later one as 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1759)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Antirrhinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaucum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="305">A. glaucum</emphasis>
L. (1759)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
